Major James Coldwell has become premier of the FLP majority.

# TODO: Major James Coldwell should be able to be premier of a Grand Coalition, Weimar Coalition, or FLP majority after Douglas dies.


@woodsworths_dilemma
title: There is no clear governing majority.
subtitle: Monarch J. S. Woodsworth faces a dilemma.
view-if: monarch == "J. S. Woodsworth" and (grand_coalition < 50 or grand_coalition_failed == 1)

Monarch J. S. Woodsworth faces a dilemma. He desperately desires a socialist or at least democratic government, but the electoral results are not there for such. Article 48 has been used by George V to promulgate anti-democratic and anti-worker policies; can Article 48 be used for good as well as evil?

- @new_elections: We will have new elections.
- @new_grand_coalition
- @left_coalition
- @popular_front_coalition
- @scp_majority


@no_confidence_elections_new
on-arrival: {!
Q.in_emergency_government = 1;
Q.no_majority_elections += 1;
Q.next_parl_election_month = Q.month + 6;
Q.next_election_time = Q.time + 6;
if (Q.next_parl_election_month > 12) {
    Q.next_parl_election_month -= 12;
    Q.next_parl_election_year = Q.year + 1;
} else {
    Q.next_parl_election_year = Q.year;
}
Q.pro_republic -= 5;
Q.workers_flp -= 3;
Q.new_middle_flp -= 3;
Q.old_middle_flp -= 3;
Q.rural_flp -= 3;
Q.catholics_flp -= 3;
Q.workers_scp += 5;
Q.old_middle_scp += 3;
Q.new_middle_scp += 3;
Q.rural_scp += 3;
Q.unemployed_scp += 5;
if (Q.pro_republic < 45 && Q.pro_republic >= 38) {
    Q.workers_flp -= 6;
}
if (Q.pro_republic < 38) {
    Q.workers_flp *= 0.85;
    Q.new_middle_flp -= 5;
    Q.old_middle_flp -= 5;
    Q.rural_flp -= 5;
    Q.catholics_flp -= 3;
    Q.workers_scp += 5;
    Q.old_middle_scp += 5;
    Q.new_middle_scp += 5;
    Q.rural_scp += 5;
    Q.unemployed_scp += 5;   
}
!}
view-if: no_confidence_votes > 50

The next elections are set for [+ next_parl_election_month : month +] [+ next_parl_election_year +].


@no_confidence_win
view-if: no_confidence_votes <= 50
on-arrival: in_minority_government = 1; in_emergency_government = 0;
achievement: minderheitsregierung

We have won the vote of no confidence, and are currently ruling under an FLP minority government. Now our task is to fix the country.


@weimar_coalition
title: We can form a Weimar Coalition.
subtitle: FLP + PPS + [+ lps_name +] [? if sapd_formed and cp_relation >= 30 : + SAPD toleration ?] ([+ weimar_coalition +]%)
view-if: weimar_coalition >= 50
on-arrival: leverage += 5; leverage += 5 if pps_party_leader == "Joos"; in_weimar_coalition = 1; flp_in_government = 1; in_popular_front = 0; in_left_front = 0; foreign_minister_party = "PPS"; interior_minister_party = "PPS"; justice_minister_party = lps_name; labour_minister_party = "PPS"; rcmp_minister_party = "I"; economic_minister_party = lps_name; finance_minister_party = "PPS"; agriculture_minister_party = "PPS"; foreign_minister = "Wirth"; interior_minister = "Wirth"; justice_minister = "Koch-Weser"; labour_minister = "Stegerwald"; rcmp_minister = "Groener"; economic_minister = "Dietrich"; finance_minister = "Köhler"; agriculture_minister = "Hermes";
achievement: weimar_coalition

We have enough votes to form a "Weimar Coalition" government consisting of the FLP, PPS and Democratic ([+ lps_name +]) parties! This has been our preferred governing coalition since 1919.

Who should be the premier?

- @douglas
- @woodsworth
- @williams_coalition_premier
- @coldwell
- @pps_premier
- @pps_premier_wirth

@williams_coalition_premier
title: George Hara Williams for Premier
subtitle: Williams is viewed as friendlier towards the left of the FLP.
view-if: year >= 1930
on-arrival: premier = "Williams"; premier_party = "FLP";
go-to: ministries

George Hara Williams has been appointed premier.


@grand_coalition
title: We can form a Grand Coalition.
view-if: grand_coalition >= 50 and grand_coalition_failed == 0
subtitle: FLP + PPS + [+ lps_name +] + CPS ([+ grand_coalition +]%)
on-arrival: in_grand_coalition = 1; in_popular_front = 0; in_left_front = 0
go-to: grand_coalition_flp_lead if (n_elections <= 1 and largest_party == "FLP") or (largest_party == "FLP" and flp_r >= 30) or monarch = "J. S. Woodsworth"; grand_coalition_pps_lead if monarch != "J. S. Woodsworth" and ((n_elections > 1 and flp_r < 30) or (n_elections <= 1 and largest_party != "FLP"))

# TODO: if there are enough votes to form a grand coalition, who leads? Does the FLP lead or does Brüning (PPS) lead? In reality this depended on George V's will, basically, which in turn depended on what his camarilla supported.
# In the first election, FLP always leads. In subsequent elections, if flp_r >= 29 then FLP leads, otherwise PPS leads?

@grand_coalition_pps_lead
go-to: grand_coalition_pps_lead_2 if cps_relation >= 30; grand_coalition_fail if cps_relation < 30

There are enough votes to form a majority coalition consisting of the FLP, PPS, Democratic ([+ lps_name +]), and People's (CPS) parties. Given our rather weak electoral performance, [? if flp_no_confidence = 1 : and our previous vote of no confidence against the government, ?][? if no_confidence_against_flp = 1 : and the vote of no confidence against us, ?] Monarch George V has asked the PPS Party to take the lead role in forming a government.

# TODO: if the FLP participated in bringing down the previous government via a vote-of-no-confidence, or if we were essentially removed from government by our coalition partners, we should be more reluctant to participate in a new government.

@grand_coalition_pps_lead_2

The PPS premier is likely to be Heinrich Brüning of the PPS Party [? if premier = "Brüning" : again. ?][? if premier != "Brüning": . ?] He is known for his conservatism and sympathy for monarchism, being on the right wing of the PPS. [? if austerity >= 2 : Due to the government's austerity policies, many of our members are reluctant to participate in this coalition again. Some support a "toleration" arrangement in which we will provide outside support to prevent the far-right from either entering government or calling a successful no-confidence vote. Others support entering into pure opposition, and letting the right do what it wishes. ?]

Brüning is not opposed to a coalition with us. Alternatively, we could enter a "toleration" agreement.

- @join_bruning: Join the Brüning coalition.
- @bruning_oppo: Join the opposition.
- @toleration_bruning: We will "tolerate" a minority Brüning government.
- @unity_government

@join_bruning
view-if: grand_coalition >= 50 or neo_weimar_coalition >= 50
on-arrival: flp_in_government = 1; flp_toleration = 0; in_grand_coalition = 1; premier = "Brüning"; premier_party = "PPS"; foreign_minister_party = "CPS"; interior_minister_party = "PPS"; justice_minister_party = "PPS"; labour_minister_party = "PPS"; rcmp_minister_party = "I"; economic_minister_party = "PPS"; finance_minister_party = "PPS"; agriculture_minister_party = "PPS"; leverage = 25 if leverage >= 25;
go-to: ministries

Heinrich Brüning welcomes us into his new cabinet. Now, we have our pick of ministries.

@bruning_oppo
on-arrival: flp_in_government = 0; flp_toleration = 0; premier = "Brüning"; premier_party = "PPS"; foreign_minister_party = "CPS"; interior_minister_party = "PPS"; justice_minister_party = "PPS"; labour_minister_party = "PPS"; rcmp_minister_party = "I"; economic_minister_party = "PPS"; finance_minister_party = "PPS"; agriculture_minister_party = "PPS"; grand_coalition_failed = 1

By refusing to join the grand coalition or tolerating it, we essentially throw the balance of government to the right wing. [? if right_coalition >= 50 : There are enough votes to form a right-wing coalition that includes the SCP. However, the SCP leader, Hugenberg, is opposed to a coalition with the "November criminals" of the PPS Party. And of course, the SCP is not interested in coalition government. This means that there will not be enough votes to form a majority coalition. ?][? if right_coalition < 50 : There are not enough votes to form a right-wing coalition that includes the SCP, and they are not interested in joining in a coalition with the "November criminals" of the PPS Party, anyhow. And of course, the SCP is not interested in coalition government. This means that there is no route to a majority coalition. ?]

If we do not at least "tolerate" the government, there will be new elections in a few months. In the meantime, the Monarch and Premier may use the emergency powers granted by Article 48 of the constitution to essentially govern by decree. And it is not at all clear that we will do any better in the next election.

- @join_bruning: Join the Brüning coalition.
- @toleration_bruning: We will tolerate Brüning after all.
- @woodsworths_dilemma
- @new_elections: New elections, it is!


@new_elections
on-arrival: {!
Q.next_parl_election_month = Q.month + 3;
Q.next_election_time = Q.time + 3;
if (Q.next_parl_election_month > 12) {
    Q.next_parl_election_month -= 12;
    Q.next_parl_election_year = Q.year + 1;
} else {
    Q.next_parl_election_year = Q.year;
}
if (Q.premier == "Brüning") {
    Q.pps_relation -= 5;
    Q.cps_relation -= 5;
}
Q.pro_republic -= 8;
Q.workers_flp -= 5;
Q.new_middle_flp -= 5;
Q.old_middle_flp -= 5;
Q.rural_flp -= 5;
Q.catholics_flp -= 3;
Q.new_middle_cps -= 8;
Q.old_middle_cps -= 8;
Q.new_middle_lps -= 5;
Q.old_middle_lps -= 10;
Q.rural_scp -= 5;
Q.workers_scp += 5;
Q.old_middle_scp += 6;
Q.new_middle_scp += 6;
Q.rural_scp += 6;
Q.unemployed_scp += 5;
// Thresholds are kind of arbitrary - adjusted because of negative economic effects on pro_republic
if (Q.pro_republic < 45 && Q.pro_republic >= 36) {
    Q.workers_flp -= 6;
}
if (Q.pro_republic < 36) {
    // TODO: if you pursue a consistently revolutionary course, you might avoid this? But you might also cause a coalition between Needham and the PPS.
    Q.pps_relation -= 5;
    Q.cps_relation -= 5;
    Q.workers_flp *= 0.85;
    Q.unemployed_flp -= 2;
    Q.new_middle_flp -= 5;
    Q.old_middle_flp -= 5;
    Q.rural_flp -= 5;
    Q.catholics_flp -= 3;
    Q.workers_scp += 8;
    Q.old_middle_scp += 8;
    Q.new_middle_scp += 8;
    Q.rural_scp += 8;
    Q.unemployed_scp += 8;   
}
if (Q.scp_majority >= 50) {
    Q.ful_strength += 100;
    Q.kkk_strength += 100;
    Q.coup_progress += 3;
}
!}

There is no path to a workable Assembly majority or minority government. The next elections are set for [+ next_parl_election_month : month +] [+ next_parl_election_year +].

The people's faith in democracy is shaken by this ordeal. Of course, the SCPs are exploiting the instability to claim that democracy is unworkable, and that Saskatchewan needs a strong leader.


@toleration_bruning
choose-if: neo_weimar_coalition >= 50
unavailable-subtitle: The parties supporting Brüning do not have a majority.
on-arrival: flp_in_government = 0; flp_toleration = 1; minority_government = 1; premier = "Brüning"; premier_party = "PPS"; foreign_minister_party = "CPS"; interior_minister_party = "PPS"; justice_minister_party = "I"; labour_minister_party = "PPS"; rcmp_minister_party = "I"; economic_minister_party = lps_name; finance_minister_party = "CPS"; agriculture_minister_party = "PPS"; pro_republic -= 4; new_middle_cps -= 5; new_middle_lps -= 5; old_middle_cps -= 5; old_middle_lps -= 5; old_middle_scp += 5; new_middle_scp += 5; rural_scp -= 5;

We have decided to tolerate Brüning's government. This means that we will vote against no-confidence votes to make sure they fail, but also that we will not be directly participating as ministers in the government. Thus, we can prevent a new election and stop the far right from entering government.

@grand_coalition_fail
on-arrival: grand_coalition_failed = 1

Unfortunately, the CPS are unwilling to enter into another coalition with the FLP, so the grand coalition is unable to be formed.

- @no_majority: Thus, there is no clear majority.
- @woodsworths_dilemma
- @right_coalition_2: Perhaps a right-wing coalition may form.
- @beg_cps: Perhaps we could ask the CPS to change their minds?
- @unity_government
- @coalition_menu: What are the other governing arrangements?


@beg_cps
view-if: cps_relation >= 15
go-to: cps_conservative if stresemann_dead == 1; cps_majority if stresemann_dead == 0

@cps_majority
go-to: join_bruning

Under the influence of Gustav Stresemann, the CPS agrees to allow us into the coalition.


@cps_conservative

The CPS asks us to adhere to their conservative economic policies (that is, extreme austerity and labour discipline) in exchange for us joining the coalition.

- @beg_cps_2: But they would not have a majority without the FLP! The SCP have no interest in participating in government.
- @no_majority: There is no chance that we would agree.
- @woodsworths_dilemma
- @coalition_menu: What are the other governing arrangements?


@beg_cps_2
go-to: beg_cps_succeed; beg_cps_fail

We make the case that without the FLP, there is no parliamentary majority, given the SCP hostility to constitutional government.

@beg_cps_succeed
go-to: join_bruning

Somehow, we succeed in convincing them! We are now in a coalition.


@beg_cps_fail
go-to: no_majority

As expected, the CPS is too set in their anti-democratic ways.



@grand_coalition_flp_lead
on-arrival: leverage -= 15 if cps_relation < 20

As expected, the FLP is the largest party, and this time, we are expected to take the lead role in the formation of the next government, including selecting the premier. Monarch [+ monarch +] has asked us to form a majority coalition with the PPS, Democratic ([+ lps_name +]), and People's (CPS) parties.

[? if cps_relation < 20 : As our relation with the CPS is poor, they are demanding more minister posts in order to remain part of the coalition. ?]

Who should be the premier?

- @douglas
- @woodsworth
- @coldwell
- @pps_premier
- @pps_premier_wirth
- @no_govt


@douglas
title: Tommy Douglas for Premier
view-if: douglas_dead = 0
subtitle: Douglas is popular within the party, and is the preferred candidate of the PPS and other parties.
on-arrival: flp_in_government = 1; premier = "Douglas"; premier_party = "FLP"; in_grand_coalition = 1 if in_weimar_coalition == 0
go-to: ministries

Douglas's appointment as premier is approved by all our potential allies.

@coldwell
title: Major James Coldwell for Premier
view-if: douglas_dead = 1
subtitle: Major James Coldwell is a party leader, but can he also be premier?
on-arrival: flp_in_government = 1; premier = "Coldwell"; premier_party = "FLP"; in_grand_coalition = 1 if in_weimar_coalition == 0
go-to: ministries

Major James Coldwell's appointment as premier is approved by our potential allies.

@woodsworth
title: J. S. Woodsworth for Premier
view-if: not historical_mode or not flp_prussia
subtitle: J. S. Woodsworth is currently the Minister-Monarch of City Police, and is one of our most popular leaders. However, other parties may have qualms about concentrating too much power in one man.

The PPS party has significant qualms about appointing J. S. Woodsworth as premier, given that he is already Minister-Monarch of City Police. They ask for either more cabinet positions, or for J. S. Woodsworth to resign his state government role. The latter is completely unacceptable.

- @douglas
- @coldwell
- @woodsworth_2: Let the PPS have their cabinet positions.

@woodsworth_2
subtitle: J. S. Woodsworth will be Premier.
view-if: not historical_mode
on-arrival: flp_in_government = 1; premier = "J. S. Woodsworth"; premier_party = "FLP"; leverage -= 10; in_grand_coalition = 1 if in_weimar_coalition == 0
go-to: ministries

We have promised to let the PPS have more influence in the government in response to the appointment of J. S. Woodsworth as premier.


@pps_premier
title: Let the PPS Party have their premier.
subtitle: Heinrich Brüning will be premier. This is unexpected and will cause internal dissent, but may give us a better position in negotiating for other cabinet positions.
on-arrival: left_dissent += 5; agrarian_dissent += 5; labour_dissent += 5; pps_relation += 10; cps_relation += 5; cp_relation -= 5; in_grand_coalition = 1 if in_weimar_coalition == 0; premier = "Brüning"; premier_party = "PPS"; flp_in_government = 1; leverage += 5
go-to: ministries

This is highly unexpected, and many in the left and agrarian of our party are criticizing this decision.

[? if year == 1932 : Since James Anderson resigned, Heinrich Brüning has been appointed premier. ?]
[? if year > 1932: Heinrich Brüning of the PPS Party has been appointed premier. ?]

@pps_premier_wirth
title: Let Joseph Wirth of the PPS Party be premier.
view-if: pps_party_leader == "Joos"
subtitle: Wirth is on the left wing of the PPS Party. This may give us a better position in negotiating for other cabinet positions.
on-arrival: left_dissent += 2; pps_relation += 6; lps_relation += 3; cp_relation -= 5; in_grand_coalition = 1 if in_weimar_coalition == 0; premier = "Wirth"; premier_party = "PPS"; flp_in_government = 1; leverage += 5
go-to: ministries




@no_govt
title: We do not form the government.
subtitle: This will cause significant internal dissent, and will lead to increased distrust from the bourgeois parties.
on-arrival: reformist_dissent += 5; agrarian_dissent += 5; labour_dissent += 5; neorevisionist_dissent += 5

Are we sure about not participating in government? This will cause significant internal dissent, and will lead to increased distrust from the bourgeois parties. Even debating this option causes internal backlash. In addition, it is possible that the bourgeois and right-wing parties will also be unable to form a coalition government, leading to a regime appointed by Monarch [+ monarch +].

- @douglas
- @woodsworth
- @pps_premier
- @no_govt_goals: Yes, we're sure.

@no_govt_goals

What are our goals here, exactly?

- @majority: We hope to reach a socialist majority in the next election.
- @trap: It is a trap to form a government now. We would be unable to accomplish our goals.
- @socialism: Revolutionary socialism is our goal.

@majority
go-to: no_govt_2

@trap
on-arrival: radicalization += 1
go-to: no_govt_2

@socialism
go-to: no_govt_2


@no_govt_2
on-arrival: reformist_dissent += 25; agrarian_dissent += 10; labour_dissent += 25; neorevisionist_dissent += 25; in_weimar_coalition = 0; in_grand_coalition = 0; premier = "Brüning" if premier == "James Anderson"; flp_in_government = 0; grand_coalition_failed = 1
go-to: right_coalition_post_flp if right_coalition >= 50 and monarch != "J. S. Woodsworth" and year < 1929; new_elections_flp if (right_coalition < 50 or year >= 1929) and monarch != "J. S. Woodsworth"; woodsworths_dilemma if monarch == "J. S. Woodsworth"


@right_coalition_post_flp
go-to: right_coalition_2

@new_elections_flp
on-arrival: next_election_time = time+3; next_parl_election_month = month + 3; next_parl_election_year = year; next_parl_election_year = year + 1 if next_parl_election_month > 12; next_parl_election_month = next_parl_election_month - 12 if next_parl_election_month > 12; new_middle_flp -= 5; old_middle_flp -= 5; workers_flp -= 3; catholics_flp -= 3; in_election = 1

Since the remaining bourgeois and right-wing parties cannot form a tolerable governing agreement, new elections have been called for [+ next_parl_election_month : month +] [+ next_parl_election_year +]. The previous premier has resigned, and has been replaced by Heinrich Brüning, also of the PPS Party, ruling as part of a monarchial cabinet. 

We are seen as responsible for the failure to form a government, and many of our middle-class and even some working-class supporters have deserted the party.


@ministries

We can pick from any number of ministries. Controlling a ministry allows us to directly effect policy in that area. [? if in_left_front : Any ministry that we do not take will be given to the CP. ?] [? if in_left_front and rcmp_minister_party == "CP" : If the CP controls the RCMP Ministry, the army will most likely revolt. ?]

